<HEADLINE> Iraqi Vice-Premier Visits Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Vice-Premier Tariq Aziz
arrived here on Sunday on a four-day working visit, the Itar-Tass
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Aziz's visit to Moscow is made "in the framework of Russia's
efforts to settle the situation around Iraq," Russian Deputy
Foreign Minister and the Russian president's special
representative for Middle East Viktor Posuvalyuk was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the Iraqi vice-premier is expected to meet
with Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov and then with Prime
Minister Yevgeny Primakov on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Interfax news agency, one of the main goals
of the visit is to discuss how to settle the crisis over Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Russia is expected to urge Baghdad to strictly abide by all
Security Council resolutions and resume full cooperation with the
U.N. special commission on Iraq's disarmament, the Interfax said.
</P>
<P>
Russia will also reiterate its readiness to insist on an early
lifting of the sanctions, imposed by the international community
on Iraq seven years ago, sources in the Russian Foreign Ministry
was quoted as reporting.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting UNSCOM chief Richard Butler on
Friday, Ivanov said Russia's task was to prevent a new crisis
around Iraq, seek a constructive solution to the remaining
problems and ease the tension in the Gulf region.
</P>
<P>
He thought that a considerable part of the U.N. commission's
work had been completed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
