<HEADLINE> URGENT  Former Israeli Foreign Minister Refuses to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Former Israeli Foreign
Minister David Levy said he will not return to the coalition
government of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, local TV reported
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Israel's Channel One quoted Levy as telling Israel Radio
a moment ago that the negotiations over the return of his
Gesher party to the coalition has led to nowhere.
</P>
<P>
No other details are available.
</P>
<P>
Moderate Levy resigned as foreign minister in January in
protest over the deadlock in the peace talks with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Levy's party decided last month to return to the government
after gaining some concessions from Netanyahu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
