<HEADLINE> Ethiopian PM Visits Djibouti </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister
Meles Zenawi returned home Sunday evening after paying a one-day
visit to neighboring Djibouti.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Meles Zenawi discussed with Djiboutian
President Hassan Gouled Aptidon and other senior government
officials on ways of further bolstering the existing ties between
the two countries, reported the Ethiopian News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Meles also visited the Djibouti Port and the Ethio-Djibouti
Railway Company in Djibouti.
</P>
<P>
After the outbreak of Ethio-Eritrean border dispute in early
May this year, Ethiopia has diverted from Eritrea's Assab Port to
the Port of Djibouti as its transport outlet.
</P>
<P>
Seventy percent of Ethiopia's exported and imported goods used
to transit through Assab, which was one of Ethiopia's two
seaports before the independence of Eritrea in May 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
