<HEADLINE> Iraqi Official: U.S. Seeking Control Over Arab </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The United States is seeking to
impose control over the Arab Nation, warned Iraqi Vice President
Taha Yassin Ramadhan on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ramadhan made the remarks when meeting with a delegation of
the International Federation of Arab Workers Unions headed by the
federation's Secretary Hassan Jammam, the Iraqi News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Ramadhan appreciated the prominent role the
federation played in supporting Iraq's steadfastness and struggle
against "the foes' hostile schemes," said the agency report.
</P>
<P>
Ramadhan said that Arab workers stood in the forefront of the
educated section facing the U.S. arrogance.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi leader called for backing to the Arab economy,
improving the workers' occupation and facilitating their travel
among the Arab countries, saying that these requirements would be
accomplished just when the Nation would have free economy.
</P>
<P>
He underscored that Iraq, after eight years of U.N. trade
embargo, managed to bypass the weakness in achieving a set of
projects and now the enemies' hidden targets have been revealed.
</P>
<P>
Ramadhan was referring to a statement made by the U.S.
President Bill Clinton in mid-November in which Clinton openly
said that America would support the Iraqi opposition to topple
the current Iraqi government led by President Saddam Hussein.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Jammam expressed the Arab workers' solidarity
with the people of Iraq, stressing that the federation had
reiterated its support for Iraq through the mass media and
conferences. 
</P>
</TEXT>
