<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Calls for End to Faction Fightings in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim,
Secretary General of the Organization of African Unity (OAU), on
Sunday strongly urged factions concerned in the Anjouan conflict
"to immediately put an end to these senseless fightings."
</P>
<P>
According to an OAU press communique issued here, Salim said
in a statement on the situation prevailing in the Comorian Island
of Anjouan that he is "greatly concerned with the unfolding
developments in Anjouan and the loss of lives and other
casualties as a result of fightings which erupted between
factions in the Island".
</P>
<P>
"These developments are all the more unfortunate as they occur
at a time when there were signs of hope for the convening of the
Comorian Inter-Islands Conference," he said.
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief noted that senseless fightings "can only bring
about further suffering and destruction," and urged factions
concerned to "seize the opportunity of the envisaged Comorian
Inter-Islands Conference to peacefully address the problems
facing the Comorian Islands and their people."
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief also appealed to member states, especially the
countries of the region to consider possibilities of extending
the necessary assistance to contribute toward an early return of
normalcy in the Indian Ocean island and the restoration of peace,
security and stability in the Island. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
