<HEADLINE> Annan Arrives in UAE to Attend Gulf Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, December 6 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan arrived here Sunday evening to attend the summit of the Gulf
Cooperation Council (GCC), the first U.N. chief to partake in the
regional meeting.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the GCC member states will review the recent
developments in the region and unify stands in various fields at
the summit, which is to open Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
South African President Nelson Mandela, who arrived here Sunday
afternoon, timed his visit to the United Arab Emirates (UAE) to
the summit. He will make a speech at the summit.
</P>
<P>
Secretary General of the Organization of Islamic Conference
Ezzidine Laraki and chief of Arab League Ahmed Esmat Abdel-Meguid
are also to take part in the summit with an aim to boost regional
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers of the GCC member states have finalized the
summit agenda which includes a wide range of political, economic,
military and social issues.
</P>
<P>
Ahead of the summit, the UAE have imposed very strict security
measures around Intercontinental Hotel where the summit will be
held and hotels where the delegations will be accommodated.
</P>
<P>
The GCC, a regional political and economic alliance set up
in 1981, groups Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia and
the UAE. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
