<HEADLINE> At Least 18 Killed in Germany Weekend Traffic Incidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 6 (Xinhua) -- At least 18 people were killed and
hundreds injured alone over the weekend in traffic accidents in
Germany as Winter held much of Europe in its grip.
</P>
<P>
On this weekend Germany was under a beautiful but dangerous
snow. The heavy snow or icy covered roads leading to more than
thousands traffic accidents.
</P>
<P>
Four elderly Germans were killed and scores of others injured
Saturday evening when their coach from Munich, Germany, plunged
down a ravine near the Austrian city of Linz, police said..
</P>
<P>
Several people were killed in weather-related accidents in the
states of Bavaria, North-Rhine Westphalia, Mecklenburg-West
Pommeria, Lower Saxony and Brandenburg.
</P>
<P>
On Germany's highest mountain peak, Zugspitze, temperatures
dropped to minus 20 degrees Celsius, according to a report of the
DPA. 
</P>
