<HEADLINE> Young Chinese Man Without Legs Doing Well in College </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Tang Yue, a young man in the
city of Chongqing who lost his legs three fingers of his left hand
in a railway accident on his way home from primary school 20 years
ago, says he is doing quite well two months into college life.
</P>
<P>
Tang finished primary and secondary school by being carried on
his parents' backs for nine years. But he began going to school by
himself by holding two stools in his hands when he entered senior
high school.
</P>
<P>
He passed the college entrance exams this July, 20 points above
the cutoff grade. But, no college would accept him because of his
amputations.
</P>
<P>
Then, some municipal government officials helped him start his
studies at a higher education institute two months ago and school
authorities have provided help by arranging a first-floor
dormitory and reducing fees. And, a factory in the city that makes
prosthetic devices has fixed him up with artificial limbs free of
charge.
</P>
<P>
Tang has adapted well to college life in two months and can
bathe himself and wash his clothes and clean his room all by
himself.
</P>
<P>
"A lot of people have shown love and care for me, which makes
me feel that I am part of a large family. I believe that I will be
able to do something for others someday," Tang says.  
</P>
</TEXT>
