<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Day No Surprises for Asiad Volleyball Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The first day for the
volleyball matches of the 13th Asian Games went smoothly on Monday
as the stronger teams took the chance to fully demonstrate their
strength.
</P>
<P>
In the men's competitions, the Chinese team beat the Indians in
straight sets 15-9, 15-7 and 15-11.
</P>
<P>
In other men's matches, the South Koreans and the Kazakhs beat
their weak opponents of Qatar and Pakistan in three sets, while
Thailand defeated its neighbor Indonesia 3-1.
</P>
<P>
The women's competitions also went without any upsets. The
Japanese and South Korean girls were proved too strong for their
counterparts from Kazakhstan and Chinese Taipei. Both teams won
in straight sets.
</P>
<P>
The men's teams from Chinese Taipei and Japan, and the women's
team from Thailand are the biggest gainers Monday as their
opponents, Mongolia and Iran, withdrew their teams from the Games'
volleyball tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
