<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Law-Enforcement Offices Giving Up Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held here
today for the hand-over of the last 30 companies owned by
provincial law-enforcement departments in China's Guangdong
province.
</P>
<P>
The local law-enforcement departments in Guangdong have given
all their businesses to the provincial government in response to a
central government order in October that said that all military,
police and law-enforcement units had to get out of the business
sector and hand over all their industrial and commercial entities.
</P>
<P>
Since October, local law-enforcement departments in Guangdong
have handed over 377 companies, closed 736 firms, and cut their
ties to 333 enterprises that had been doing business under the
name of a certain law-enforcement body. 
</P>
</TEXT>
