<HEADLINE> OAU Organ Calls for End to Faction Fighting in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Central Organ of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) Mechanism for Conflict
Prevention, Management and Resolution Monday called for an
immediate end to the faction fighting in the Comorian island of
Anjouan.
</P>
<P>
The warring sides were also urged to commit themselves to
peaceful solution of the crisis within the framework of the peace
process initiated by the OAU.
</P>
<P>
An OAU press release issued here said, the Central Organ held
an urgent meeting at ambassadorial level in Addis Ababa Monday on
the deteriorating security situation prevailing in the Indian
Ocean island.
</P>
<P>
A communique issued after the meeting said the Central Organ
expressed its grave concern over the unfolding events in Anjouan,
the loss of lives and other casualties caused by the fighting.
</P>
<P>
The Central Organ called on the countries of the region to
response positively to the request of the government of the
Comoros, in order to assist in the restoration of normalcy,
peace, security and stability in Anjouan.
</P>
<P>
The Central Organ also reiterated in the communique its
unflinching commitment to the unity, territorial integrity and
sovereignty of the Comoros. 
