<HEADLINE> Spring City's Fight Against Industrial Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Environment Protection Bureau
of Jinan, the capital of east China's Shandong Province, took
steps today to stop industrial pollution to protect its famous
springs.
</P>
<P>
An official says that the bureau will do a thorough check on
projects that use kilns and boilers through the 20th of January,
and that enterprises that do not meet environmental protection
standards will face severe penalties.
</P>
<P>
Jinan has had rapid industrial development in recent years, but
the neglect of environmental protection by some enterprises has
led to serious pollution that endangers the beauty of the city's
springs.  
