<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Alternative Energy Expands 30 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The amount of electricity from
alternative renewable energy sources in Germany grew 30 percent
last year to five billion kilowatt hours, the Association of
German Electrical Power Utilities (VDEW) said Monday.
</P>
<P>
But the amount represents only about one percent of the total
electricity consumption in Germany, the VDEW noted.
</P>
<P>
The biggest renewable energy source was the wind-power, which
contributed 2.9 billion kilowatt hours of electricity to Germany,
up from two billion kilowatt hours in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Hydro-electric power production reached 1.5 billion kilowatt
hours in 1997 from 1.3 billion in 1996 while biomass-based fuels
produced 600 million kilowatt hours, up from 500 million in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Solar energy output rose to 7.6 million kilowatt hours from 4.5
million in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981207.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern China Asking Investors To Help Urban Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investors have been
invited to help the capital of China's Guangdong Province,
Guangzhou, build urban infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Vice-mayor Li Zhuobin informed a discussion group today about
the prospects of cooperation between Guangzhou and international
companies.
</P>
<P>
After decades of construction, the southern Chinese city is
ranked one of the 10 best cities in China in urban infrastructure,
traffic facilities, public utilities, housing, and environmental
protection, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Four billion U.S. dollars have been put into Guangzhou's
infrastructure by overseas investors, but more overseas funds are
needed since the city plans to host the Ninth National Sports
Games by 2001, he says, and 165 billion yuan is expected to be
spent on the city's infrastructure and environmental protection in
the next three years.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be used for the first phase of Guangzhou's new
International Airport, 12 sewage treatment plants, and other
projects, he says.  
</P>
</TEXT>
