<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Monday closed at 2,921.80
points as against last close of 2,849.82, netting a gain of 71.98
points.
</P>
<P>
The national index spurted by 32.22 points to 1,298.71 from
previous close of 1,266.49.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar index were quoted substantially
up at 301.23 and 117.81 points compared with last weekend closing
of 294.10 and 115.10 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities rallied smartly lifting the sensitive index by 71.98
points on the stock market Monday in the wake of fresh buying by
operators coupled with sustained and heavy purchases by foreign
institutional investors and domestic institutions. 
