<HEADLINE> Head Of China's Supreme Court Meets With Pakistan Chief Justice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Xiao Yang, president of China's
Supreme People's Court, met with Ajmal Mian, chief justice of
Pakistan's Supreme Court, Mrs. Mian and their party here today.
</P>
<P>
Xiao said China's current judicial reforms are intended to
bring justice to the judiciary and that they are needed for the
development of a socialist market economy. He briefed the guests
on China's open trial and jury system.
</P>
<P>
He also said that China will maintain its own characteristics
but can learn valuable experience and good methods from Pakistan
and other countries.
</P>
<P>
Chief Justice Mian also gave an account on Pakistan's judicial
system and said he hopes to increase exchanges and cooperation
with China. 
</P>
