<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Railway Company Targets Property Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The State Railway of Thailand
(SRT) is overhauling its regulations to make the most of property
development on its 250,000-rai (40,000 hectares) land nationwide,
Thai News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The revamp would start with adjusting the assessed prices of
its land to attract more private investors.
</P>
<P>
At present, the prices are as much as 20 percent higher than
the reference prices of the Land Department and this discourages
developers regarding high rents based on the assessed prices.
</P>
<P>
Particularly under the current economic situation, the assessed
prices should be reduced to lure investment.
</P>
<P>
The current assessed prices discourage about 500 land leases of
the SRT from renewing their contracts. If they were adjusted and
those contracts were extended, the SRT would generate over 10
million baht (270,000 U.S. dollars) immediately.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the SRT is planning to hire the private sector to
collect rents from its land leases and to manage property
development on its land.
</P>
<P>
The move should generate more income from the SRT's land
because the state enterprise was facing difficulties in collecting
rents and managing its property due to insufficient personnel.
</P>
<P>
The SRT management will present the land development proposal
to its board of directors for approval.
</P>
<P>
If the proposal is endorsed, the SRT will enjoy more income by
simply collecting benefit and seeing its private contractors
develop its land on its behalf. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
