<HEADLINE> AIDS Rampages in Swaziland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 50 percent of
people who tested HIV positive in the land-locked Swaziland were
between the ages of 10 and 24, said a report reaching here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report was to mark the World AIDS Day which fell on
December 1, but was published in Mbabane, capital of Swaziland,
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Only eight percent of those who tested HIV positive said they
or their partners used condoms regularly, and 37 percent admitted
to never using condoms.
</P>
<P>
HIV is precursor of killer AIDS, the acquired immune
deficiency syndrome.
</P>
<P>
The report said 76 percent admitted having sex outside
marriage and over half of those had sex with multiple partners.
</P>
<P>
Most of the infected students, aged between 15 and 18, were
sent for tests by parents, rather than volunteering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
