<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Opposes All Forms of Arms Race: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will continue to
oppose all forms of arms race, including nuclear arms
proliferation, President Shahabuddin Ahmed said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We believe in the policy of good neighborly and friendly
relations and malice to none, and we oppose all aggressive
policies and activities," the president said in a speech to
officials and cadets at the Bangladesh Air Force (BAF) Academy in
Jessore, some 150 kilometers southwest of here.
</P>
<P>
The country is determined to eradicate poverty and raise the
living standards of the common people, Ahmed said. "Amid all
limitations, we have created an efficient defense system to
safeguard our sovereignty and protect dignity as a respected
nation," the official BSS news agency quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
Gradual steps have been taken for modernizing the defense
system and pragmatic steps have been taken for creating a strong
and expanded air force, the president noted. He added that
sophisticated equipment would be added to the BAF and the
country's defense system would be strengthened to boost its
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Though Bangladesh is a country belonging to the Third World and
lacks sophisticated equipment, BAF pilots should receive
world-class training and have first-class theoretical knowledge,
he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged soldiers and officers of BAF to be ready for supreme
sacrifices for the sake of the nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
