<HEADLINE> S. African Clothing Giant Opens Branches in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 7 (Xinhua) -- South African clothing
giant, "Mr. Price", announced Monday that it has made a
significant expansion in Namibia this year.
</P>
<P>
Three stores, two in the capital of Windhoek and one in
eastern Gobabis, were opened in November following the openings
in northern Otjiwarongo in September and in western Walvis Bay
earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Alastair Mcarthur, managing director of Speciality Stores
which owns Mr. Price and other four chain clothing stores, said
in a statement that the openings in Windhoek last weekend were
the best in the history of the Mr. Price Group.
</P>
<P>
"The downtown Windhoek store achieved a turnover of more than
250,000 Rand (about 42,000 U.S. dollars) on each of its first
three trading days," Mcarthur said.
</P>
<P>
The success in Namibia had encouraged the group to speed up
its international expansion plans for the Mr. Price brand, with
an opening program set to start in Botswana early in the new
year, he said. 
</P>
