<HEADLINE> Two Chinese Mathematicians Awarded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Two Chinese mathematicians
today won the sixth Shiing Shen Chern Maths Award, which is
used to praise young and middle-aged Chinese mathematicians for
their significant research achievements.
</P>
<P>
The two mathematicians were Wen Lan, a professor with Beijing
University, and Wang Jianpan, a professor with the Shanghai-based
East China Teachers' University. Their research achievements both
have gained high evaluation in the international mathematics
field.
</P>
<P>
The Shiing Shen Chern Maths Award, named after a noted Chinese
mathematician, was sponsored and funded by Y. K. Lau, president of
the Elite Industrial Holdings Ltd of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The biennial prize awards two mathematicians with each
gaining 25,000 HK dollars (about 3,200 U.S. dollars). Some 12
Chinese mathematicians have been awarded Since the first Shiing
Shen Chern Maths Award was given in 1987.  
</P>
</TEXT>
