<HEADLINE> China Cutting Cost Of Rural Electricity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- China plans to cut the cost of
rural electricity by improving rural power grids and standardizing
urban and rural costs in the next three years, a State Development
Planning Commission official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made by the State Council and is expected to
save farmers 18 billion yuan in costs annually for peasants.
</P>
<P>
Rural electricity costs are higher on average than urban costs
because of old rural power grids, illegal electricity fees, and
poor management.
</P>
<P>
The official says that correcting this will help peasants'
lives and agriculture.  
</P>
