<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Jobless Rate Stable in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)
unemployment rate remained at 9.8 percent in October, the same as
in September, Eurostat reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The EU unemployment rate dropped to below 10 percent for the
first time in six years in September when it fell to 9.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate in the single-currency euro zone -- composed
of France, Germany, Italy, Spain, Belgium, the Netherlands,
Luxembourg, Portugal, Austria, Finland and Ireland -- dropped to
10.8 percent in October from 10.9 percent the previous month.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat, the EU's Luxembourg-based statistical bureau, said
that the lowest unemployment rates were found in Luxembourg and
the Netherlands at 2.2 percent and 3.7 percent respectively
while the highest rate was in Spain at 18.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
EU-wide, the jobless rate was 10.6 percent in October last year
and 10.8 percent in October 1996.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat estimated that 14.1 million people were without a job
in the euro zone while the jobless totalled 16.8 million in the
European Union as a whole.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rates for people under the age of 25 were 19.1
percent in the European Union and 21.1 percent in the euro zone.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981207.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Import of Opium Pipes Is Offense: HK Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 7 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Customs
and Excise Department stressed Monday that it is an offense to
bring into Hong Kong opium pipes, which violates the Dangerous
Drugs Ordinance.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ordinance, no person shall have in his
possession any pipe, equipment or apparatus, fit and intended for
the smoking, inhalation, ingestion or injection of a dangerous
drug.
</P>
<P>
Any person who contravenes the ordinance shall be guilty of an
offense and on conviction is liable to a fine of 10,000 HK dollars
(1,282 U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
