<HEADLINE> Chinese Divers Open Impressive Gold Bids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese divers opened their
impressive bids for golds in the ongoing Asian Games here on
Monday when they made a clear sweeping of the one-two spots in the
obligatory dives of the men's platform and women's three-meter
springboard.
</P>
<P>
Tian Liang, 19, platform silver medallist in the World
Championships in Perth, Australia in January, finished first with
180.420 points after the first four dives.
</P>
<P>
His 14-year-old teammate Huang Qiang followed in second in
176.760. Ken Terauchi of Japan was third in 173.970.
</P>
<P>
Chinese diving coach Zhou Jihong said Terauchi will be the man
for her proteges to beat in the optional competitions.
</P>
<P>
"Terauchi is an experienced diver with much renown," she said,
"He'll bring some troubles to both Tian and Huang in the optional
dives"
</P>
<P>
Guo Jingjing, a 19-year-old teenager, garnered 230.970 points
in the women's three-meter springboard after five obligatory
dives.
</P>
<P>
Her teammate Yang Lan, also 19, came in second in 208.710.
Ok-Rim Ri of DPR Korea was third in 206.430. Kazakhstan's much
heralded Irina Vyguzova placed fourth temporarily in 201.600.
</P>
<P>
The optional dives of men's platform and women's three-meter
springboard will be held on Tuesday. 
</P>
