<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Disburses 1.4B Dollars of ODA capital in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has disbursed 1.4 billion
U.S. dollars of official development assistance (ODA) this year,
380 million dollars more than last year, Vietnam News Agency (VNA)
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
This means 4.8 billion dollars of ODA, or 44 percent of the
total ODA committed for Vietnam in the 1993-1997 period, has been
disbursed so far in the country, VNA said.
</P>
<P>
About 20 nations, 15 international organizations and 300
non-governmental organizations pledged a combined 10.8 billion
U.S. dollars of ODA for Vietnam through five donors' conferences
held from 1993-1997.
</P>
<P>
Ten percent of the sum is in the form of aid, and the rest soft
loans.
</P>
<P>
The largest share of ODA flows in socio-economic
infrastructural development, especially in the sectors of power,
land roads, irrigation, education and training, health care and
environment.
</P>
<P>
The sixth conference of ODA donors for Vietnam is to open in
Paris Monday (December 7).
</P>
<P>
The two-day conference will focus on agricultural and rural
development and hunger eradication and poverty alleviation in
Vietnam, VNA quoted Minister of Planning and Investment Tran Xuan
Gia who now is in Paris as saying.
</P>
<P>
ODA flow into Vietnam will decrease, the minister said.
However, he stressed that ODA commitment to Vietnam is not only a
source of material assistance but also the international
community's acceptance of Vietnam's policy, thus the commitments
themselves bear a higher value than their value in money. 
</P>
</TEXT>
