<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila to Assist 3 Filipino Workers in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government said
Monday that it will extend all possible assistance, including
legal services, to three overseas Filipino workers (OFWs)
implicated in the killing of a compatriot in Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Presidential spokesman Jerry Barican told reporters here that
the victim was identified as Rocaya Bangon while her suspected
killer is Danilo Espino, also an OFW, who is now under detention.
</P>
<P>
Two other OFWs - Edna Perido and Pedro Ramos -- are facing
investigation in connection with the case, he said.
</P>
<P>
Barican said that the Department of Foreign Affairs (DFA) "has
instructed the Philippine Embassy in Kuwait to provide all
possible assistance, including the hiring of a defense counsel,
for the accused Espino, and possibly, Perido and Ramos."
</P>
<P>
He said Espino has confessed to killing Bangon while Perido and
Ramos, based on preliminary reports from the Philippine Embassy in
Kuwait, are being investigated, either as witnesses to or
participants in the crime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
