<HEADLINE> ADB Delegation Visits Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD December 7 (Xinhua) -- A three-member delegation of
the Asian Development Bank (ADB) arrived here Monday to discuss
future funding for Pakistan's development projects.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will discuss future programs, particularly those
to be executed next year, sources at the ADB resident mission
said.
</P>
<P>
It will also discuss the financial package of 5.5 billion U.S.
dollars recently reached with the International Monetary Fund,
sources added.
</P>
<P>
Mahsud Ali Shah, member of the ADB delegation, will assume his
new assignment in Islamabad from January 18 next year, replacing
the current program manager Frank Polman.
</P>
<P>
Presently, there are about 47 ongoing projects of the ADB in
this South Asian nation which would also come under review of the
visiting delegation.
</P>
<P>
According to the ADB sources, the ADB is satisfied with the
implementation of the bank's funded projects in Pakistan despite
economic difficulties facing the country in the post-economic
sanctions scenario this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
