<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Fund Industry Sees Net Inflows for Second Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Investment
Funds Association (HKIFA) said Monday that the unit trust
industry saw a net inflow of 45.58 million U.S. dollars in October,
up by 48.8 percent over September's inflow of 30.64 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The key reason for the robust inflow in October was strong
investor interest in bond funds, said a press release issued by
HKIFA on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The bond sector attracted new money of 69.97 million U.S.
dollars in October, representing 70 percent of its gross inflows.
</P>
<P>
As to why bond funds were so popular, Desmond Chan, chairman of
 the HKIFA, said that since the outbreak of the Asian currency
crisis last year, it seems that investors have in general found
bonds more attractive than equities, especially on a risk and
return basis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
