<HEADLINE> Chinese Gymnasts Further Enlarge Leads after Four Apparatus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- World champions China further
enlarged their lead after the fourth rotation of the men's team
final at the gymnastics tournament of the 13th Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
China collected a total points of 153.050 after four apparatus of
vaulting horse, parallel bars, high bar and floor exercises, followed
by Japan in the second place at 150.925 points and South Korea
in the third in 150.600 respectively.
</P>
<P>
