<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Run Up on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices ran up on the
Singapore Stock Market Monday on rising expectations that interest
rates will trend lower further.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) moved up 19.69 points
to close at 1,376.82 points with blue chips firmer and broad
market weaker.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover dropped to 167.26 million units valued at
303.26 million Singapore dollars (about 182.96 million U.S.
dollars). Decliners edged out advancers by 151 to 98 with 171
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The IDT was the most active stock of the day with a turnover of
10.62 million units traded. It was followed by Van DH which had a
turnover of 8.78 million units done. IPCO was next with 8.34
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH headed the ascent of the day with a 80 cent jump to 17.30
Singapore dollars. OCBC F surged 55 cents to end at 10.30
Singapore dollars. RothmansI also moved up 55 cent but finished at
9.60 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Seaview led the descent of the day with a loss
of 36 cents to 4.16 Singapore dollars. AMatrix shed 27 cents to
close at 1.07 Singapore dollars. Transmarco sank 21 cents to end
at 2.63 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said Monday's rise was encouraged by Friday's rally on
Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
They also said expectations of a recovery in corporate earning
growth next year also stoked buying.
</P>
<P>
But they noted the market was dominated by a mood of caution
amid fears of a sharp correction in New York stocks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
