<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Monday as profit taking on
finance stocks led the decline.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index fell 12.48
points to 514.78, the all-share Emas Index slipped 4.09 points to
140.05, the Industrial Index dipped 23.87 points to 992.81,
finance stocks, which led the day's market fall, dragged the
Finance Index 130.80 points lower to 3,510.20, and the Second
Board Index slipped 7.12 points to 181.70.
</P>
<P>
Losers overwhelmed gainers by 679 to 92 while 62 counters were
unchanged, 86 untraded and 49 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover declined to 679.141 million shares valued at
1.149 billion ringgit (about 302.368 million U.S. dollars) from
last Friday's 859.959 million shares worth 1.273 billion ringgit
(about 335 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Main Board turnover slipped to 590.932 million shares
valued at 888.073 million ringgit (about 233.703 million dollars)
from 756.463 million shares worth 992.271 million ringgit (about
261.123 million dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Second Board turnover was also lower at 88.209 million
shares worth 260.819 million ringgit (about 68.636 million
dollars) from 103.535 million shares valued at 280.861 million
ringgit (about 73.91 million dollars) last Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
