morning in a fire engulfing a house of the retirees in Livry
Gargan in Seine-Saint-Denis north of Paris.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out in a room of the house at around four
o'clock before spreading to other parts of the three-story house,
said firemen.
</P>
<P>
Three people were killed and 21 injured in another fire in
Paris in the day.
</P>
<P>
About 100 people were evacuated to a nearby hotel and a cafe
from the devastated house located in the ninth district of Paris,
said the police.
</P>
<P>
It took several hours for firemen to put down the fire. 
