<HEADLINE> Philippines Starts Education Week Celebration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Department of Education,
Culture and Sports (DECS) of the Philippines Monday started its
celebration of Education Week, which this year commemorates the
centennial of the creation of the department.
</P>
<P>
Under a 1985 presidential proclamation, Education Week is
celebrated every second week of December to mark the signing of
the 1863 Educational Decree, which reorganized the Spanish
colonial educational system and established primary instruction
and normal schools for Filipino teachers.
</P>
<P>
The proclamation states that Education Week should aim to
recognize the objectives, programs and accomplishments under the
educational system and honor the contribution of public and
private school teachers.
</P>
<P>
This year's theme, Education for All: Focus on the 100th
Anniversary of DECS Creation, marks the role of the department in
training and molding young minds as good citizens and future
leaders since 1898, Victor Andres Manhit, Undersecretary of the
department, said.
</P>
<P>
One of the highlights of this year's Education Week celebration
is to award three public school officials on December 8 at the
Presidential Palace, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
