<HEADLINE> South Korea Beat Japan 2-0 in Asiad Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- South Korea beat Japan 2-0 in a
match between the 2002 World Cup co-hosts at the 13th Asian Games
soccer tournament on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean team, which surprisingly lost to Turkmenistan
2-3 in group match, proved they still had an upper hand over their
long-time arch-rivals Japan.
</P>
<P>
Physically stronger than their Japanese counterparts, the South
Korean team played aggressively and got awarded at the 30th minute
when Japanese goal-keeper fouled down South Korean forward.
</P>
<P>
Star forward Choi Yong-Soo, who took part in the World Cup
finals, made no mistake from the spot to put South Korea 1-0
ahead.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, the South korean team continued their
domination with fierce defence and effective counter-attacks.
</P>
<P>
It was Choi Yong-Soo again who added a killing touch to a quick
counter-attack at the 53rd minute to wrap up the match 2-0 for
South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Though losing the match, the Japanese team still have the
chance to advance into the quarter-finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
