<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan's Guchsha Wins Men's Free Pistol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan's Vladimir Guchsha
won the Asian Games men's free pistol shooting here on Monday,
scoring 657.8 points for the title.
</P>
<P>
Atlanta Olympic Games silver medalist Wang Yifu grabbed the
silver medal with 655.5 while DPR Korea's Kim Jong-Su finished
third just 0.1 points behind.
</P>
<P>
"After the qualification round I was very confident that I
would win the gold medal," said 31-year-old Guchsha after the
competition. "During the final I lost my confidence for a while
but quickly regained it."
</P>
<P>
Wang, who at 38 helped China won the world championship in
July, said: "I did not produce a good performance today. I was hit
by allergic problems these days so I was not on peak form."
</P>
<P>
Another DPR Korea finalist Kim Hyon-Ung, who led Guchsha by 0.7
points before the tenth and last shot, notched a poor 5.5 points
to gave the title to Guchsha. He eventually finished fifth.
</P>
</TEXT>
