<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Leads Gymnastic Team Competition at Asiad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- World champion China jumped
ahead after the first rotation in the men's team finals of the
gymnastics competition at 13th Asian Games here Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese gymnasts collected 38.375 points from their first
apparatus of the vaulting horse, followed by Japan in second with
38.050 points in pommel horse.
</P>
<P>
South Korea and DPR Korea shared the third place on 37.475
points from the rings and the parallel bars respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese squad is composed of world champion Zhang Jingjin
and young faces of Huang Xu, Yang Wei, Xing Aowei, Li Xiaopeng and
Zhao Sheng.
</P>
<P>
The rotatition order for the defending champion China is the
vaulting horse, parallel bars, high bars, floor exercises, pommel
horse and rings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
