<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cai Rates South Korea and DPK Korea as Main Rivals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese table tennis head coach
Cai Zhenhua said on Monday that South Korea and the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea were China's arch rivals in the Asian
Games.
</P>
<P>
"In either men's or women's event, South Korea and DPR Korea
are two forces to reckon with," said Cai.
</P>
<P>
In the women's competitions, Chinese Taipei are the other team
who may upset Cai's students, the Chinese coach added.
</P>
<P>
Cai, who watched the DPR Koreans' training on Monday, said they
would give more troubles to China than the South Koreans would.
</P>
<P>
"We are very familiar with the South Korean style, but DPR
Korea have rarely made international appearance and we don't have
special tactics against them," Cai said.
</P>
<P>
Cai said the Chinese players had to accustom themselves to
air-conditioning in the court as well as to the made-in-Japan ball
which felt softer than the one Chinese used to play with. 
</P>
</TEXT>
