<HEADLINE> Liu Xiuhua Wins Women's 48kg Weightlifting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Liu Xiuhua broke the snatch
world record and got a winning total of 187.5 kilograms to win the
women's 48kg weightlifting title at the 13th Asiad here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
It was the first gold medal for China after the Asian sports
powerhouse failed to produce any gold medals in shooting and
cycling competitions earlier on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Lay Thi Win of Myanmar finished second with a total of 182.5
kilograms. Sri Indriyani of Indonesia totalled 180 kilograms for
the bronze medal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
