<HEADLINE> Fire Razes Manila Metal Works Shop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 7 (Xinhua) - A metal works shop in Manila, the
Philippines, was razed by fire Monday morning but no one was
reported injured, government officials said.
</P>
<P>
The fire started at around 11:50 in the morning but it was
declared under control at 12:15 noon.
</P>
<P>
Initial report made by the arson investigators showed that the
fire was triggered by a leaking tank.
</P>
<P>
Firemen could not determine the amount of the damage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
