<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Egyptian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Egyptian newspapers on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Al Ahram:
</P>
<P>
-- The remaining members of the Egyptian contingent in Bosnia
returned to Cairo Sunday after spending more than six years during
which they carried out peace-keeping missions in Sarajevo as part
of the United Nations forces.
</P>
<P>
The first groups of the Egyptian contingent began to arrive in
Cairo in October.
</P>
<P>
Al Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Mozambican Foreign Minister Leonardo Simao arrived in Cairo
Sunday on an official three-day visit to Egypt.
</P>
<P>
He will attend the first session of the Joint Higher
Egypt-Mozambique Committee with his Egyptian counterpart Amr
Moussa.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign minister will discuss relations between the two
countries and spheres of bilateral cooperation besides issues of
mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Al Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- Foreign Minister Amr Moussa will receive Monday American
Assistant Secretary of State for the Middle and Near East Affairs
Martin Indyk, who arrived in Cairo Sunday on a three-day visit.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the second session of Egyptian-U.S. strategic
dialogue will open in Cairo Monday under co-chairmanship of
Assistant Foreign Minister Ahmed Abu Al-Gheit and Indyk.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- President Hosni Mubarak on Sunday, before rounding up his
two-day visit in Turkey, urged business people in Egypt and Turkey
to launch joint ventures in both countries which he termed as
"pivotal" in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
In a gathering with Turkish business people joined by their
Egyptian counterparts, Mubarak laid stress on opening up new
cooperation avenues between the two countries at different
governmental and private levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
