<DOCNO> XIE19981207.0191 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Auction Bowling Alleys </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Some 100 bowling alleys under
construction in Shanghai will go on the auction block due to
slumping business.
</P>
<P>
Fan Ganping, a representative of the Shanghai International
Commodity Auction Co. Ltd., said the properties up for auction
feature equipment and lanes manufactured by U.S.-based Brunswick
in 1996. The auction will be held in the middle of December.
</P>
<P>
The rapidly rising popularity of bowling over the past few
years led to an overheated market and ill-advised investments in
related facilities.
</P>
<P>
The rapidly expanding forms of entertainment available to
Shanghainese led to a downturn in bowling enthusiasm and forced
related businesses to reduce prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
