<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan to Aid Refugees in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government on Monday
pledged to provide 3.5 million U.S. dollars to assist refugees in
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Japan's State Foreign Secretary Nobutaka Machimura announced
the pledge in a speech at the outset of a Tokyo meeting of
countries assisting strife-torn Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Of the money, 1.5 million dollars will be offered as
grant-in-aid for non-governmental organizations helping refugees
in Afghanistan, while another two million dollars will be put up
to fund refugee assistance programs in the country by some
international organizations, Machimura said.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 officials from 15 donor countries to Afghanistan are
taking part in the two-day meeting which opened here earlier in
the day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
