<HEADLINE> Moroccan Prime Minister Leaves Shanghai for Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Moroccan Prime
Minister Abderrahmane Youssoufi left here today for Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
Youssoufi and his party arrived here on Sunday from
Qingdao. Vice-Mayor Chen Liangyu met with the Moroccan guests last
night.
</P>
<P>
Youssoufi, who has visited Shanghai years ago as an official of
Casablanca city government, was impressed by the current
construction in this financial and commercial metropolis in east
China. He told the host that his country is ready to further the
cooperation with Shanghai in economic, trade and financial fields.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister and the delegation youred Lujiazui Financial
and Trade Zone during their stay. 
</P>
