<HEADLINE> Two Chinese Bow out of Snooker Competitions in Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Two Chinese snooker players
suffered their defeats on Monday, failing to book any berth in the
last eight of the tournament in the ongoing Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
Chinese top player Pang Weiguo was outclassed by Yashin
Merchant of India 5-1 in the best of nine series, while teammate
Guo Hua failed to win the decisive game and bowed out of the meet
4-5 against Keith E Boon Aun of Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Hong Kong, China, had a mixed feeling when its top
seed Marco Fu Ka-Chun was toppled by Ooi Chin Kay of Malaysia 5-3,
and second seed Chan Kwok Ming secured his place in the top eight
by beating Japanese Shinya Egashira in five straight games.
</P>
