<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Comes Back to Kremlin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
arrived in the Kremlin early Monday after a 15-day stay in the
Central Clinical Hospital where he was treated for pneumonia.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency quoted a presidential spokesman as
saying that Yeltsin was meeting chiefs of the presidential
administration.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin was hospitalized on November 22 with a temperature of
38.9 degrees Celsius and diagnosed to have pneumonia.
</P>
<P>
Presidential spokesman Dmitry Yakushkin said last Friday that
Yeltsin was well and poised to return to work in the Kremlin or
his Gorki-9 residence outside Moscow.
</P>
<P>
He said Yeltsin "is energetic, speaks very briskly, works much
and is in a cheerful mood." 
</P>
</TEXT>
