<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals Drop in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in the
Philippines dropped slightly in the first three quarters of this
year despite a steady stream of American and European travelers.
</P>
<P>
During the first nine months of this year, visitor arrivals
dropped 1.54 percent to 1,557,680 from 1,382,031 a year ago,
according to a report by the Department of Tourism.
</P>
<P>
The report showed that visitors from the United States totaled
343,735, an increase of 14.01 percent from last year's 301,492 for
the period.
</P>
<P>
Next to the United States, most of the foreign travelers who
visited the country came from Japan with 275,820 from 72,745 a
year earlier, it said.
</P>
<P>
But visitors from Asian and Pacific countries have decreased,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said while Americans and Europeans are taking the
advantage of weak local currencies by visiting Asian countries,
Asians are cutting their spending on foreign trips. 
</P>
</TEXT>
