<HEADLINE> Inflation Rate Falls in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- India's annual rate of
inflation fell to 8.13 percent for the week ended November 21, a
sharp fall for the second successive week.
</P>
<P>
As the growth rate in the prices of food articles continued to
ease, the inflation rate, based on wholesale price index, fell by
0.41 percent in the week following a decline of 0.31 percent to
8.54 percent in the previous week, the Times of India reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
However, the daily said, this decline in the overall index did
not indicate any drastic drop in prices of food articles but only
mean that the sustained increase in prices had abated.
</P>
<P>
Inflation based on consumer price index for industrial workers
was running at a huge 18.6 percent in October compared to 16.3
percent in September.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the inflation rate based on the final index for the
week ended September 26, the latest available, stood at 8.8
percent and the final index for all commodities for the week stood
at 357.1 compared to the provisional figure of 356.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the current week, indices of primary articles and
manufactured articles decline due mainly to an easing of price
rise in food articles and food products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
