two respectively in 51.01 and 51.39 seconds in the men's 100m
freestyle in Japan's National Championships in June.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old twin brothers are considered as Japanese
swimming hopefuls in the men's short-distance freestyles.
</P>
<P>
Though scraping into the men's 200m freestyle finals with an
eighth finishing time of 1:54.91 on Monday, Shusuke said with
confidence: "I'm sure to win in the finals this evening."
</P>
<P>
In the men's 200m freestyle, Shunsuke's opponent will be
Torlarp Sethothorn of Thailand and Wang Chuan of China, who
finished 1-2 in the preliminaries respectively in 1:52.77 and
1:52.97.
</P>
<P>
China's Du Jie failed to qualify for the men's 200m freestyle
finals on Monday, and Zhao Lifeng will compete in the 100m
freestyle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
