<HEADLINE> Thailand Wins Gold in Women's Air Rifle Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Thailand became the surprise
winner in the women's 10 meters air rifle team event with 1,178
points, snatching for the host country its second gold medal at
the 13th Asian Games here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Thai team, formed by Pupiromchaikul Thanyarat, Kerdsumran
Nuanwan and Dangpiam Jarintorn, also bettered the Asian Games
record of 1,172 points set by China at Beijing in 1990.
</P>
<P>
"I am very proud," said Pupiromchaikul at Hua Mark Sports
Center shooting range. "I am also excited because we have won the
gold medal."
</P>
<P>
Thai Shooting Association president Pongpol Adireksarn was
apparently overjoyed but he said it was not totally out of
expectation.
</P>
<P>
"We're hosting the games so naturally we have to find our
best," said the president. "And our shooting team have been doing
well in international competitions."
</P>
<P>
South Korea finished second at 1,171 points while world
championships runner-up China won the bronze by scoring 1,169.
</P>
<P>
"My shooters did not perform very well today," said Chinese
coach Shao Jianhua. "They were too slow entering the peak form."
</P>
