<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Six Miners Survive Trying Ordeal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The six miners who were
trapped in a mine cave-in in north China's Hebei Province for 27
days and rescued recently are out of danger thanks to treatments in
a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
On October 31, the miners were trapped when the roof of a
gypsum mine in Longyao County collapsed.
</P>
<P>
The six men were trapped in the shaft approximately 300 meters
from the mouth. The men survived by eating their leather belts and
drinking water seeping from the roof of the shaft. They also burned
any materials available to keep warm.
</P>
<P>
A rescue team finally opened the shaft on November 26, when
they all could not talk, with four suffering from low blood
pressure and one being in a coma.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the cave-in is under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
