bank will
begin releasing information about the service in the New Year. "It
will
be competitive," he said.
</P>
<P>
Cooke declined to say what encryption technology the service
will use,
but said it will be "very strong."
</P>
<P>
Russell Briant, BNZ product manager of electronic payments,
said the
bank is trying to put systems in place to allow New Zealand
merchants to
charge for goods and services sold over the Internet in foreign
currencies.
</P>
<P>
"A key priority for the bank is to meet the customer need for
multi-
currency transactions and we have been in the forefront of
producing a
solution. We have got people looking at that now," he said.
