<HEADLINE> Kashi Prefecture Completes Airport Expansion Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- An airport expansion project in
Kashi Prefecture of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region, passed a state appraisal today after nearly 15 months'
work.
</P>
<P>
The prefecture which borders on five neighboring countries,
including Pakistan, has developed into an attractive tourist area
famous for its integration of Islamic, western and eastern
cultures.
</P>
<P>
The airport project, completed at a cost of 200 million yuan,
is a key national project which will continue to promote border
trade in the region.
</P>
<P>
Completion of the project has provided the airport with the
capacity to service large airliners, including Boeing 747s.
</P>
</TEXT>
