<HEADLINE> Poland, Slovakia Agree to Share Winter Olympics Bid for 2006 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The Polish and Slovak Olympic
committees agreed Sunday to put in a joint bid for the 2006
Winter Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Poland's favorite skiing resort, Zakopane, near the country's
southern border with Slovakia, is bidding to host the 2006 Winter
Olympics.
</P>
<P>
As part of Sunday's agreement, Slovakia's Chopok mountain,
also in the Tatra range, would be the site of the downhill, the
local evening news program Wiadomosci said.
</P>
<P>
Wiadomosci added that Zakopane is ready to share some other
events with Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
Much of the Zakopane area is in the Tatra National Park,
established in 1954 to protect plants and wildlife. It was
designated a natural reserve by the United Nations Educational,
Scientific and Cultural Organization in 1992. 
