<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tension Mounts Before Polls in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- More clashes were reported on
Sunday in northwestern Bangladesh's Pabna district before a
by-election to be held there on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At least five people were injured in clashes between supporters
of the ruling Bangladesh Awami League (BAL) and the major
opposition, the Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP).
</P>
<P>
And there were incidents of houses and poll campaign offices
being set ablaze and attacks on residences and shops, press
reports here said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Four candidates from different parties were contesting for the
seat of the Pabna-2 constituency, which was vacated following the
death of a BAL member of parliament in June this year.
</P>
<P>
The election generated much heat and the situation was very
tense in the district, as both the BAL and the BNP, the two major
political rivals in the country, had dubbed it a prestige issue,
according to the reports.
</P>
<P>
Police arrested five persons, and none of them was from the
BAL, the reports quoted local people as saying.
</P>
<P>
Police and members of the Bangladesh Rifles were seen
patrolling the sensitive villages in the Pabna-2 constituency to
ward off further violence, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,280 security guards, including 200 servicemen and 240
personnel from the Bangladesh Rifles, would be deployed to ensure
a peaceful, free and fair election.
</P>
<P>
About 188,700 people would cast their votes in 81 polling
centers, an official from the Election Commission Secretariat told
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the BNP on Sunday asked the Election Commission to
immediately withdraw three senior officials from election duty
from the constituency who they complained were working in favor of
the nominee of the ruling party.
</P>
<P>
"The election can't be fair if these officials are not
withdrawn from election duty... and steps taken to ensure
impartial polls," BNP Secretary General Abdul Manna Bhuiyan told a
press briefing Sunday evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
