<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S.Korea's Foreign Investments Increase in Past 11 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investments in South
Korea reached 6.91 billion U.S. dollars in the past 11 months of
this year, 16.4 percent higher than the same period of last year,
according to South Korean Economy and Finance Ministry Monday.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investments stood at seven billion dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
November's foreign investments included 117 cases worth 1.378
billion dollars, the second highest in history, against 76 cases
worth 91 million dollars in the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The figure was the largest monthly one since the International
Monetary Fund last December agreed to bail out South Korea from a
financial crisis caused by corporate failures and bad loans of
financial institutions with a 58-billion-dollar loan.
</P>
<P>
The ministry attributed the improved foreign investments to the
government's efforts to attract more foreign investors and the
gradual recovery of South Korea's international credibility.
</P>
<P>
It predicted that more foreign funds will flow in along with
further restructuring of key sectors like electronics,
petrochemical and tourism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
