Games track and field tournament, made these remarks after China
failed to win the Games' first gold medal in the women's marathon
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"The Japanese athletes has good expierences in training," Lou
said. "Their method is more scientific than ours. The secret
behind their success is that they have made a breakthrough in
training."
</P>
<P>
Naoko Takahashi of Japan claimed the gold with a new Asia's
best time of 2:21:47, with her compatriot Kai Tomoko placing third
in the 42.195-kilometer race.
</P>
<P>
Pre-race favorite Pan Jihong of China finished only fourth in
2:37:29, and her teammate Wang Yanfang came in a distant eighth.
</P>
<P>
"The Japanese can always achieve good results in international
competitions, but the Chinese athletes can only run well at home.
" Lou said.
</P>
<P>
" What's the use of running a good time at domestic
competitions?"
</P>
<P>
Pan entered the field with a personal best time of 2:26:39, far
ahead of her clocking in the race. 
