<HEADLINE> Dongguan Develops into China's Largest Export Processing Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Dongguan City in south
China's Guangdong Province established its processing industry in
1978 and has now developed into China's largest export
processing base.
</P>
<P>
Dongguan's 13,000 processing enterprises exported products
valued at 9.7 billion US dollars in 1997. Eleven of the world's
top 100 enterprises have invested in the city.
</P>
<P>
The city's electronics sector currently accounts for 23 percent
of its total annual exports.
</P>
<P>
A local official noted that the city's processing industry has
benefitted from infrastructure construction. The city has
allocated over 20 billion yuan for infrastructure projects over
the past two decades. Now, it has 530,000 telephone lines and an
annual power generation capacity of 10 billion KWH.
</P>
<P>
Dongguan hopes to attract more foreign investment in its
high-tech processing industry, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The city's processing sector is expected to record 11.8 billion
US dollars in export earnings in 1998. 
</P>
