and sanitation project in Sri Lanka, government sources here said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to improve the health and well-being of
about one million people in six districts of Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Rural and Urban water supply and sanitation in these districts
will be also improved under the project.
</P>
<P>
Norway is to assist in the digitized mapping of water and sewer
lines of greater Colombo, which will help reduce the water loss in
the area, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
