<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Japanese Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading Japanese newspapers Monday.
</P>
<P>
Asahi, Yomiuri, Mainichi, Nihon Keizai:
</P>
<P>
-- The largest-ever Asian Games officially opened in Bangkok on
Sunday as some 3,500 athletes and officials representing 41 Asian
national Olympic committees paraded into Rajamangala National Stadium
to kick off the 15-day event.
</P>
<P>
