<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yunnan and HK to Build Wild Animal World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- A company in the capital of
southwest China's Yunnan Province and a Hong Kong company have
signed a contract here to build the Yunnan Wild Animal World.
</P>
<P>
The project, which will cost 260 million yuan (31.4 million US
dollars), is located near Kunming's Jindian scenic spot, six
kilometers from the city, and in the initial stage, a wild animal
exposition zone and a forest tourist zone will be set up.
</P>
<P>
The animal zone, covering an area of 149 hectares will
accommodate nearly 10,000 animals of over 200 species, including
tigers, lions and bears. The 104 hectares of forest zone will
provide a place of leisure for tourists.
</P>
<P>
Part of the animal zone will be open to the public on May 1
next year to mark the opening of the World Horticulture Exposition.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan is home to 17,000 species of plants and 1,737 species of
vertebrate, which account for 62.9 percent and 54.9 percent,
respectively, of China's total species of high-class plants and
vertebrate. In Yunnan, 162 species of animals are put under the
protection of the state.  
</P>
</TEXT>
