<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Keeping Unemployment Under Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, which has a
population of 13 million, has been successful in tackling the
employment issue and keeping the jobless rate well under control.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that in 1997, the number of employees
was 8.47 million, 1.49 million more than in 1978. The unemployment
rate was three percent.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two decades, Shanghai has been engaged in
market-oriented employment reforms, increasing the number of job
channels for local people.
</P>
<P>
As the number of layoffs rises with the reforms in state
enterprises, the city government has set up re-employment
centers. In the past seven years, 1.19 million of the city's 1.4
million laid-off workers have found jobs with the help of these
centers.
</P>
<P>
The city has also created job opportunities by promoting a
range of industries like the service industry, which has hired
3.23 million people, accounting for 38.2 percent of the city's
entire work force.
</P>
<P>
The private sector has also helped by absorbing nearly 900,000
people. In 1980, only 3,600 people were employed by private
businesses.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
