<HEADLINE> Top Chinese PC Maker Cashing in on Software Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- China's largest personal
computer manufacturer, the Legend Group, set up a joint venture
software company with one of the world's leading software
developer, Computer Associates (CA) of the United States, this
week.
</P>
<P>
This is Legend's second major move to increase its exposure in
the software business, after a cooperation agreement with IBM
earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
CA is claimed to be a large software producer second only to
Mirosoft. Over 90 percent of the world's 500 biggest companies use
its products.
</P>
<P>
Legend and CA hold an equity share of 50 percent each in the
3.5 million U.S. dollar Guanqun Computer Corp. Ltd. of Beijing,
which is to develop software technology and manufacture various
related products. Over 70 percent of the company produces will be
exported.
</P>
<P>
Du Yongbo, general manager of the joint venture, says that the
company will release Chinese software called "Wending" in six
months for Chinese-language users all over the world. Their
cooperation, he says, is intended to facilitate the development of
Chinese language-based software.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, Legend has signed a cooperative agreement
with a major Chinese software developer, UFsoft (Group) Corp., and
invested in Beijing's Kingsoft software company.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that Legend will tie software to its hardware products
in order to fight piracy in the country's software market.
</P>
</TEXT>
