<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blueprint Stresses Sciences in Farming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Science and
Technology is working on guidelines to help increase agricultural
production and fatten farmers' wallets.
</P>
<P>
According to today's China Daily, the move is a response to the
just-concluded Third Plenary Session of the 15th Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China. The session emphasized "promoting
agricultural science and the technological revolution,"
</P>
<P>
The ministry will concentrate more on stepping up
agro-technology innovations, accelerating agricultural
modernization and spreading technology in rural areas, especially
in the central and western regions of China.
</P>
<P>
In addition to broadening and deepening the nation's
agricultural producers' skills, dissemination agencies
set up under the previous planned economy, regional scientific and
technological departments will, in line with the market economy,
encourage more technology service companies to provide farmers
with modern farming skills.
</P>
<P>
Advanced information technologies, such as global positioning
systems and remote-sensing technologies, will be added to improve
meteorological and natural disaster forecasting efficiencies in
the agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
More computerized networks will be made available to distribute
updated agricultural technologies and to advise farmers of the
lastest market demands.
</P>
<P>
The daily quoted Vice-Minister Han Deqian as saying that more
efforts will be made to develop biotechnology, especially
technologies related to the cultivation of genetically altered
crops.
</P>
<P>
The world had an average of 35 million hectares of genetically
altered crops last year. China lags behind developed countries in
growing such crops but tops the world in cultivating hybrid maize,
wheat and rice.
</P>
<P>
The country has made breakthroughs in growing pest-resistant
tomatoes through the gene manipulation technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981207.0310 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
