<HEADLINE> China's Largest Private Business Getting Larger Feed Market Share </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- While many of China's feed
manufacturers are suffering this year, the Hope Group continues to
grow month by month to have a 10-percent share in the domestic
feed market.
</P>
<P>
The largest private group of China with headquarters in
Chengdu, Sichuan Province, said that its sales is expected to
reach 3.3 million tons this year, compared with last year's three
million tons.
</P>
<P>
Sales in the feed industry plummeted 16 percent from last
year. Analysts say that a drop in the price of pigs and a smaller
number of pigs being raised are to blame.
</P>
<P>
Hope Group President Liu Yonghao said the reason his company is
able to buck the general trend is that the group has put a lot of
effort into tapping the potential of rural markets.
</P>
<P>
It also took advantage of the possibilities when foreign
companies began withdrawing from the China market because of the
Asian financial turmoil and took control of some areas they
originally controlled.
</P>
<P>
Pig feed is Hope's major product, but the company is also
developing poultry food and fish food.  
</P>
</TEXT>
