<HEADLINE>   Ocalan Willing to Accept International Trial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Kurdish rebel leader Abdullah
Ocalan said here Sunday that he will accept any decision over his
case made by Italy or European Union, if the international
community pledges to take concrete steps to resolve the Kurdish
issue.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan told Italian news agency ANSA that an Italian-backed
proposal for him to be tried in an international court would be
the best possible solution.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan was arrested by Italy after flying into Rome from Moscow
on November 12. As the leader of Kurdistan Worker Party, he is
Turkey's most wanted man.
</P>
<P>
Italy's rejection over Turkish demands for his extradition has
caused a crisis in relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan also explained Sunday that his only desire is to win
"the respect of the entire Kurdish population and the political
recognition of their problem within Turkey."
</P>
<P>
But he reiterated that now he wants to find a peaceful
solution to the issue.
</P>
<P>
"Now things have changed and we are ready to stop the
fighting," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan is currently under house arrest in Rome on the basis of
a German warrant, but Germany has said that it will not request
his extradition and the warrant will expire on December 22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
