<DOCNO> XIE19981207.0320 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police Impersonators Arrested in Northern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Police in the city of Taiyuan,
capital of Shanxi Province in northern China, recently uncovered a
group of criminals who had been committing robberies, rapes and
burglaries while disguised as police since October 1997.
</P>
<P>
A special taskforce was set up by the Taiyuan Public Security
Bureau this September to deal with the case, and five of the key
members of the ring have been arrested. They and their accomplices
were found to have been responsible to 151 crimes and the murder
of one of their members.
</P>
<P>
Police also confiscated some forged official seals and ID cards
of the public security bureaus of Taiyuan and Hohhot, capital of
the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, that were used by the fake
policemen.
</P>
<P>
They were discovered to have police uniforms they had bought or
stolen, as well as home-made pistols, daggers, electric batons,
cars, mobile telephones, pagers, and jewelry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
