<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Expects to Reach This Year's Export Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The hefty increase in
Shanghai's exports in the first ten months of this year will lead
to a fulfilment of the year's target, the Municipal Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation Commission said over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai exported 13.77 billion U.S. dollars worth of goods
from January to October, up 10.16 percent from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
With the encouraging performance, said commission head Zhu
Xiaoming, the city is sure that it can reach its export target of
16.3 billion U.S. dollars for the year.
</P>
<P>
According to him, 46.7 percent of the city's exports for the
January-October period were from overseas-financed businesses.
</P>
<P>
Although Shanghai's exports to other parts of Asia suffered a
decline of 7.14 percent to 6.1 billion U.S. dollars in the ten
months, an increase of 20 percent was recorded in its exports to
Europe and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Because of the Asian financial crisis, exports slowed down a
great deal this year, Zhu said, and he believes that Shanghai
needs to come up with a strategy for increasing medium- and
high-quality exports, with emphasis on new products and high-tech
products in particular.
</P>
<P>
The city will develop new measures to increase exports by
encouraging private companies and scientific research institutes
to get involved in foreign trade, and letting medium-sized and
small enterprises get foreign trade approval more quickly.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
