<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Newcastle Draws Middlesbrough in English Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 6 (Xinhua) -- One late goal from Greek
defender Nikos Dabizas gave Newcastle United a 2-2 draw against
Middlesbrough at the English Premier League on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Middlesbrough had lost their previous four north-east league
derbies but seemed set for a victory after having the best of
things at the Riverside Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Andy Townsend shot them ahead after 13 minutes after Paul
Gascoigne picked him out with a clever corner but Frenchman
Laurent Charvet deservedly equalised with a fierce volley from
the edge of the box seven minutes before halftime.
</P>
<P>
Boro took charge in the second half but Brian Deane and
Townsend were both foiled by stand-in goalkeeper Steve Harper.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old was making his first appearance for Newcastle
after spending five years waiting for his chance and made it
memorable by scooping Deane's point-blank header on to the bar
and then brillianty tipping Townsend's drive round the post.
</P>
<P>
However, he could do little about Middlesbrough's second in
the 59th minute when Colin Cooper's tame shot took a hefty
defelection and looped into the net.
</P>
<P>
Middlesbrough, who conceded a late goal a week ago to draw at
Arsenal, then sat back and paid the price when substitute Dabizas
was left unmarked to loop in a header in the 84th minute.
</P>
<P>
Middlesbrough remain seventh in the standings, six points
behind leaders Aston Villa. Newcastle stay 13th. 
</P>
</TEXT>
