<HEADLINE> People Under Investigation For Yangtze Levee Break </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Three officials of Gong'an County
in central China's Hubei Province are being investigated by the
county procuratorate for dereliction of duty during this summer's
devastating floods on the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, when the Yanjiatai section of the
Yangtze River Levee appeared to be under threat from July 20 to
25, the three officials were nowhere to be found. When they were
informed of the possibly imminent danger, they took no steps to
reinforce the levee, which then collapsed on August 7.
</P>
<P>
This resulted in water flooding into a 346-sq.km. area with 3
towns and 63 villages, where 135,000 people were affected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981207.0336 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Peacekeepers in Angola Freed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Angola's opposition
UNITA on Sunday allowed 14 U.N. peacekeepers to evacuate,
according to a U.N. statement released here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA)
had finally given permission for an aircraft to land to pack up
the peacekeepers, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
They are currently in safety at the U.N. Observer Mission in
Angola's regional headquarters in Huambo, it added.
</P>
<P>
UNITA had blocked the evacuation of the peacekeepers about a
month ago in retaliation for the refusal of the Angolan government
to allow the United Nations to fly to UNITA areas to resupply the
peacekeepers.
</P>
<P>
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan hopes very much that the
release of U.N. personnel would encourage all concerned to
proceed with full implementation of the Lusaka protocol, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
The protocol, aimed to end nearly two decades of civil war in
the African country, was signed in Lusaka, Zambia, between the
Angolan government and UNITA in 1994 and is currently monitored by
over 1,000 U.N. peacekeepers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981207.0337 </DOCNO>
