<HEADLINE> Northeastern Chinese Province Promoting Border Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Heilongjiang
Province has had 1.15 million foreign tourists, mainly from
Russia, since 1988, when it first opened its border tourism with
Russia.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official says that Heilongjiang got 200
million U.S. dollars worth of foreign exchanges from tourism in
the past decade.
</P>
<P>
The province has a 3,004-kilometer border with Russia, and 15
ports along the border. There are nearly 40 travel agencies in the
province with travel routes to Russia.
</P>
<P>
The province's border tourism business gets 80 percent of its
foreign customers from Russia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
